{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Raise Stamp Duty threshold to \u00a3500k for residential purchases long term",
        "additional_details": "The sector is under distress with banks, HMLR, HMRC, surveyors developers and bulk providers all having significant delays and backlogs.\r\n\r\nTransactions taking longer due to COVID.\r\n\r\n2016 SDLT deadline created significant issues and market was functioning correctly.\r\n\r\nLocal business benefit from increased activity in the market - removal companies, trades etc.\r\n\r\nMore VAT related items purchased.\r\n\r\nFormalising the current payment holiday will allow the sector to reconfigure.",
        "background": "The current SDLT payment holiday introduced as part of the COVID-19 measures to stimulate the economy is due to end on on the 31st March 2021.\r\nMany property professionals consider that it has created a cliff edge that will have a significant adverse impact on the sector and wider economy.",
